notesStmt.note: Paper: Visible laid lines with chain lines in groups of 3.

msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Commentary on the Zīj Gūrgānī, also known as the Zīj-i jadīd-i Sulṭānī, which comprised tables of calendar calculations, trigonometry, planets, and stars compiled from observations made at the observatory in Samarqand, completed in 1447. The tables themselves are not included.

supportDesc.extent: 409 leaves : 177 x 128 (111 x 72) mm. bound to 177 x 138 mm

collation.p: Paper, 409 + i; 41 gatherings, alternating between 8 and 12 leaves, with 1 extra leaf added to the last gathering; [1-409], modern foliation in pencil, upper left recto. Catchwords on each leaf, lower left verso.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 15 long lines; frame ruled.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a naskh script in black ink; pointed.

decoDesc.decoNote: Numerous diagrams in red ink; rubrications in red.

binding.p: Contemporary red leather with flap (Type II), blind-stamped central mandorla on covers and flap; marbled paper doublure.

origin.p: Copy completed in A.H. 899 (1493-1494, colophon, f. 409r).

history.provenance: Formerly owned by Muḥammad ibn Jaʻfar Yaḥyá (stamp, f. 1v, 409r).
Sold by Sam Fogg Ltd. (London) to Lawrence J. Schoenberg, Dec. 2000.
Deposit by Lawrence J. Schoenberg and Barbara Brizdle, 2011.
